BEGIN_PGML

[@ image("UBC-BME-18-044.png", width=>[$width], height=>[$height]) @]*

The patellar tendon attaches to the tibia at the tibial tuberosity. The tibial tuberosity is [`d=[$d]`] [`cm`] from the center of the knee joint (*a*). The patellar tendon pulls at an angle of [`\theta=[$theta]^{\circ}`] to a line passing through the tibial tuberosity and the center of the knee joint. If the patellar tendon produces an extension torque around the knee joint equal to [`[$t]`] [`Nm`], how large is the force, [`F_p`], in the patellar tendon?

[`F_p=`] [_____]{"$fp"} [`N`]  

